v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

26// Adds Mips-specific methods to convert InstructionOperands.
27class MipsOperandConverter final : public InstructionOperandConverter {
28 public:
29 MipsOperandConverter(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
30 : InstructionOperandConverter(gen, instr) {}
31
32 FloatRegister OutputSingleRegister(size_t index = 0) {
33 return ToSingleRegister(instr_->OutputAt(index));
34 }
35
36 FloatRegister InputSingleRegister(size_t index) {
37 return ToSingleRegister(instr_->InputAt(index));
38 }
39
40 FloatRegister ToSingleRegister(InstructionOperand* op) {
41 // Single (Float) and Double register namespace is same on MIPS,
42 // both are typedefs of FPURegister.
43 return ToDoubleRegister(op);
44 }
45
46 Register InputOrZeroRegister(size_t index) {
47 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) {
48 DCHECK_EQ(0, InputInt32(index));
49 return zero_reg;
50 }
51 return InputRegister(index);
52 }
53
54 DoubleRegister InputOrZeroDoubleRegister(size_t index) {
55 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) return kDoubleRegZero;
56
57 return InputDoubleRegister(index);
58 }
59
60 DoubleRegister InputOrZeroSingleRegister(size_t index) {
61 if (instr_->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate()) return kDoubleRegZero;
62
63 return InputSingleRegister(index);
64 }
65
66 Operand InputImmediate(size_t index) {
67 Constant constant = ToConstant(instr_->InputAt(index));
68 switch (constant.type()) {
69 case Constant::kInt32:
70 return Operand(constant.ToInt32());
71 case Constant::kInt64:
72 return Operand(constant.ToInt64());
73 case Constant::kFloat32:
74 return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat32());
75 case Constant::kFloat64:
76 return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat64().value());
77 case Constant::kExternalReference:
78 case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject:
79 case Constant::kHeapObject:
80 // TODO(plind): Maybe we should handle ExtRef & HeapObj here?
81 // maybe not done on arm due to const pool ??
82 break;
83 case Constant::kRpoNumber:
84 UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(titzer): RPO immediates on mips?
85 }
86 UNREACHABLE();
87 }
88
89 Operand InputOperand(size_t index) {
90 InstructionOperand* op = instr_->InputAt(index);
91 if (op->IsRegister()) {
92 return Operand(ToRegister(op));
93 }
94 return InputImmediate(index);
95 }
96
97 MemOperand MemoryOperand(size_t* first_index) {
98 const size_t index = *first_index;
99 switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
100 case kMode_None:
101 break;
102 case kMode_Root:
103 *first_index += 1;
104 return MemOperand(kRootRegister, InputInt32(index));
105 case kMode_MRI:
106 *first_index += 2;
107 return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputInt32(index + 1));
108 case kMode_MRR:
109 // TODO(plind): r6 address mode, to be implemented ...
110 UNREACHABLE();
111 }
112 UNREACHABLE();
113 }
114
115 MemOperand MemoryOperand(size_t index = 0) { return MemoryOperand(&index); }
116
117 MemOperand ToMemOperand(InstructionOperand* op) const {
118 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(op);
119 DCHECK(op->IsStackSlot() || op->IsFPStackSlot());
120 return SlotToMemOperand(AllocatedOperand::cast(op)->index());
121 }
122
123 MemOperand SlotToMemOperand(int slot) const {
124 FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(slot);
125 return MemOperand(offset.from_stack_pointer() ? sp : fp, offset.offset());
126 }
127};
128
129static inline bool HasRegisterInput(Instruction* instr, size_t index) {
130 return instr->InputAt(index)->IsRegister();
131}

135class OutOfLineRecordWrite final : public OutOfLineCode {
136 public:
137 OutOfLineRecordWrite(CodeGenerator* gen, Register object, Register index,
138 Register value, Register scratch0, Register scratch1,
139 RecordWriteMode mode, StubCallMode stub_mode)
140 : OutOfLineCode(gen),
141 object_(object),
142 index_(index),
143 value_(value),
144 scratch0_(scratch0),
145 scratch1_(scratch1),
146 mode_(mode),
147#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
148 stub_mode_(stub_mode),
149#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
150 must_save_lr_(!gen->frame_access_state()->has_frame()),
151 zone_(gen->zone()) {
152 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, index, scratch0, scratch1));
153 DCHECK(!AreAliased(value, index, scratch0, scratch1));
154 }
155
156 void Generate() final {
157 __ CheckPageFlag(value_, scratch0_,
158 MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq,
159 exit());
160 __ Daddu(scratch1_, object_, index_);
161 SaveFPRegsMode const save_fp_mode = frame()->DidAllocateDoubleRegisters()
162 ? SaveFPRegsMode::kSave
163 : SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore;
164 if (must_save_lr_) {
165 // We need to save and restore ra if the frame was elided.
166 __ Push(ra);
167 }
168 if (mode_ == RecordWriteMode::kValueIsEphemeronKey) {
169 __ CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode);
170#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
171 } else if (stub_mode_ == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
172 // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
173 // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched when the code
174 // is added to the native module and copied into wasm code space.
175 __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode,
176 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
177#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
178 } else {
179 __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode);
180 }
181 if (must_save_lr_) {
182 __ Pop(ra);
183 }
184 }
185
186 private:
187 Register const object_;
188 Register const index_;
189 Register const value_;
190 Register const scratch0_;
191 Register const scratch1_;
192 RecordWriteMode const mode_;
193#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
194 StubCallMode const stub_mode_;
195#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
196 bool must_save_lr_;
197 Zone* zone_;
198};

221Condition FlagsConditionToConditionCmp(FlagsCondition condition) {
222 switch (condition) {
223 case kEqual:
224 return eq;
225 case kNotEqual:
226 return ne;
227 case kSignedLessThan:
228 return lt;
229 case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
230 return ge;
231 case kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
232 return le;
233 case kSignedGreaterThan:
234 return gt;
235 case kUnsignedLessThan:
236 return lo;
237 case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
238 return hs;
239 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
240 return ls;
241 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
242 return hi;
243 case kUnorderedEqual:
244 case kUnorderedNotEqual:
245 break;
246 default:
247 break;
248 }
249 UNREACHABLE();
250}
251
252Condition FlagsConditionToConditionTst(FlagsCondition condition) {
253 switch (condition) {
254 case kNotEqual:
255 return ne;
256 case kEqual:
257 return eq;
258 default:
259 break;
260 }
261 UNREACHABLE();
262}
263
264Condition FlagsConditionToConditionOvf(FlagsCondition condition) {
265 switch (condition) {
266 case kOverflow:
267 return ne;
268 case kNotOverflow:
269 return eq;
270 default:
271 break;
272 }
273 UNREACHABLE();
274}
275
276FPUCondition FlagsConditionToConditionCmpFPU(bool* predicate,
277 FlagsCondition condition) {
278 switch (condition) {
279 case kEqual:
280 *predicate = true;
281 return EQ;
282 case kNotEqual:
283 *predicate = false;
284 return EQ;
285 case kUnsignedLessThan:
286 case kFloatLessThan:
287 *predicate = true;
288 return OLT;
289 case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
290 *predicate = false;
291 return OLT;
292 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
293 case kFloatLessThanOrEqual:
294 *predicate = true;
295 return OLE;
296 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
297 *predicate = false;
298 return OLE;
299 case kFloatGreaterThan:
300 *predicate = false;
301 return ULE;
302 case kFloatGreaterThanOrEqual:
303 *predicate = false;
304 return ULT;
305 case kFloatLessThanOrUnordered:
306 *predicate = true;
307 return ULT;
308 case kFloatGreaterThanOrUnordered:
309 *predicate = false;
310 return OLE;
311 case kFloatGreaterThanOrEqualOrUnordered:
312 *predicate = false;
313 return OLT;
314 case kFloatLessThanOrEqualOrUnordered:
315 *predicate = true;
316 return ULE;
317 case kUnorderedEqual:
318 case kUnorderedNotEqual:
319 *predicate = true;
320 break;
321 default:
322 *predicate = true;
323 break;
324 }
325 UNREACHABLE();
326}

330#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_LOAD_INTEGER(asm_instr) \
331 do { \
332 __ asm_instr(i.OutputRegister(), i.MemoryOperand()); \
333 __ sync(); \
334 } while (0)
335
336#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_STORE_INTEGER(asm_instr) \
337 do { \
338 __ sync(); \
339 __ asm_instr(i.InputOrZeroRegister(2), i.MemoryOperand()); \
340 __ sync(); \
341 } while (0)

343#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(load_linked, store_conditional, bin_instr) \
344 do { \
345 Label binop; \
346 __ Daddu(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
347 __ sync(); \
348 __ bind(&binop); \
349 __ load_linked(i.OutputRegister(0), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
350 __ bin_instr(i.TempRegister(1), i.OutputRegister(0), \
351 Operand(i.InputRegister(2))); \
352 __ store_conditional(i.TempRegister(1), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
353 __ BranchShort(&binop, eq, i.TempRegister(1), Operand(zero_reg)); \
354 __ sync(); \
355 } while (0)
356
357#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(load_linked, store_conditional, sign_extend, \
358 size, bin_instr, representation) \
359 do { \
360 Label binop; \
361 __ daddu(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
362 if (representation == 32) { \
363 __ andi(i.TempRegister(3), i.TempRegister(0), 0x3); \
364 } else { \
365 DCHECK_EQ(representation, 64); \
366 __ andi(i.TempRegister(3), i.TempRegister(0), 0x7); \
367 } \
368 __ Dsubu(i.TempRegister(0), i.TempRegister(0), \
369 Operand(i.TempRegister(3))); \
370 __ sll(i.TempRegister(3), i.TempRegister(3), 3); \
371 __ sync(); \
372 __ bind(&binop); \
373 __ load_linked(i.TempRegister(1), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
374 __ ExtractBits(i.OutputRegister(0), i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(3), \
375 size, sign_extend); \
376 __ bin_instr(i.TempRegister(2), i.OutputRegister(0), \
377 Operand(i.InputRegister(2))); \
378 __ InsertBits(i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(2), i.TempRegister(3), \
379 size); \
380 __ store_conditional(i.TempRegister(1), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
381 __ BranchShort(&binop, eq, i.TempRegister(1), Operand(zero_reg)); \
382 __ sync(); \
383 } while (0)
384
385#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(load_linked, store_conditional) \
386 do { \
387 Label exchange; \
388 __ sync(); \
389 __ bind(&exchange); \
390 __ daddu(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
391 __ load_linked(i.OutputRegister(0), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
392 __ mov(i.TempRegister(1), i.InputRegister(2)); \
393 __ store_conditional(i.TempRegister(1), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
394 __ BranchShort(&exchange, eq, i.TempRegister(1), Operand(zero_reg)); \
395 __ sync(); \
396 } while (0)
397
398#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT( \
399 load_linked, store_conditional, sign_extend, size, representation) \
400 do { \
401 Label exchange; \
402 __ daddu(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
403 if (representation == 32) { \
404 __ andi(i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(0), 0x3); \
405 } else { \
406 DCHECK_EQ(representation, 64); \
407 __ andi(i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(0), 0x7); \
408 } \
409 __ Dsubu(i.TempRegister(0), i.TempRegister(0), \
410 Operand(i.TempRegister(1))); \
411 __ sll(i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(1), 3); \
412 __ sync(); \
413 __ bind(&exchange); \
414 __ load_linked(i.TempRegister(2), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
415 __ ExtractBits(i.OutputRegister(0), i.TempRegister(2), i.TempRegister(1), \
416 size, sign_extend); \
417 __ InsertBits(i.TempRegister(2), i.InputRegister(2), i.TempRegister(1), \
418 size); \
419 __ store_conditional(i.TempRegister(2), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
420 __ BranchShort(&exchange, eq, i.TempRegister(2), Operand(zero_reg)); \
421 __ sync(); \
422 } while (0)
423
424#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER(load_linked, \
425 store_conditional) \
426 do { \
427 Label compareExchange; \
428 Label exit; \
429 __ daddu(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
430 __ sync(); \
431 __ bind(&compareExchange); \
432 __ load_linked(i.OutputRegister(0), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
433 __ BranchShort(&exit, ne, i.InputRegister(2), \
434 Operand(i.OutputRegister(0))); \
435 __ mov(i.TempRegister(2), i.InputRegister(3)); \
436 __ store_conditional(i.TempRegister(2), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
437 __ BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, i.TempRegister(2), \
438 Operand(zero_reg)); \
439 __ bind(&exit); \
440 __ sync(); \
441 } while (0)

443#define ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER_EXT( \
444 load_linked, store_conditional, sign_extend, size, representation) \
445 do { \
446 Label compareExchange; \
447 Label exit; \
448 __ daddu(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
449 if (representation == 32) { \
450 __ andi(i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(0), 0x3); \
451 } else { \
452 DCHECK_EQ(representation, 64); \
453 __ andi(i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(0), 0x7); \
454 } \
455 __ Dsubu(i.TempRegister(0), i.TempRegister(0), \
456 Operand(i.TempRegister(1))); \
457 __ sll(i.TempRegister(1), i.TempRegister(1), 3); \
458 __ sync(); \
459 __ bind(&compareExchange); \
460 __ load_linked(i.TempRegister(2), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
461 __ ExtractBits(i.OutputRegister(0), i.TempRegister(2), i.TempRegister(1), \
462 size, sign_extend); \

464 sign_extend); \
465 __ BranchShort(&exit, ne, i.TempRegister(2), \
466 Operand(i.OutputRegister(0))); \
467 __ InsertBits(i.TempRegister(2), i.InputRegister(3), i.TempRegister(1), \
468 size); \
469 __ store_conditional(i.TempRegister(2), MemOperand(i.TempRegister(0), 0)); \
470 __ BranchShort(&compareExchange, eq, i.TempRegister(2), \
471 Operand(zero_reg)); \
472 __ bind(&exit); \
473 __ sync(); \
474 } while (0)

476#define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_BINOP(name) \
477 do { \
478 FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
479 __ PrepareCallCFunction(0, 2, kScratchReg); \
480 __ MovToFloatParameters(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), \
481 i.InputDoubleRegister(1)); \
482 __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::ieee754_##name##_function(), 0, 2); \
483 /* Move the result in the double result register. */ \
484 __ MovFromFloatResult(i.OutputDoubleRegister()); \
485 } while (0)
486
487#define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(name) \
488 do { \
489 FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
490 __ PrepareCallCFunction(0, 1, kScratchReg); \
491 __ MovToFloatParameter(i.InputDoubleRegister(0)); \
492 __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::ieee754_##name##_function(), 0, 1); \
493 /* Move the result in the double result register. */ \
494 __ MovFromFloatResult(i.OutputDoubleRegister()); \
495 } while (0)

497#define ASSEMBLE_F64X2_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(op) \
498 do { \
499 __ op(i.OutputSimd128Register(), i.InputSimd128Register(0), \
500 i.InputSimd128Register(1)); \
501 } while (0)

503void CodeGenerator::AssembleDeconstructFrame() {
504 __ mov(sp, fp);
505 __ Pop(ra, fp);
506}
507
508void CodeGenerator::AssemblePrepareTailCall() {
509 if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
510 __ Ld(ra, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
511 __ Ld(fp, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
512 }
513 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToSP();
514}

518void AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(MacroAssembler* masm,
519 FrameAccessState* state,
520 int new_slot_above_sp,
521 bool allow_shrinkage = true) {
522 int current_sp_offset = state->GetSPToFPSlotCount() +
523 StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountAboveFp;
524 int stack_slot_delta = new_slot_above_sp - current_sp_offset;
525 if (stack_slot_delta > 0) {
526 masm->Dsubu(sp, sp, stack_slot_delta * kSystemPointerSize);
527 state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
528 } else if (allow_shrinkage && stack_slot_delta < 0) {
529 masm->Daddu(sp, sp, -stack_slot_delta * kSystemPointerSize);
530 state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
531 }
532}

540}

548// Check that {kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister} is correct.
549void CodeGenerator::AssembleCodeStartRegisterCheck() {
550 __ ComputeCodeStartAddress(kScratchReg);
551 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongFunctionCodeStart,
552 kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, Operand(kScratchReg));
553}
554
555// Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
556// jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
557// to:
558// 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
559// the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
560// 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
561// 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
562void CodeGenerator::BailoutIfDeoptimized() {
563 int offset = InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
564 __ Ld(kScratchReg, MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
565 __ Lwu(kScratchReg, FieldMemOperand(kScratchReg, Code::kFlagsOffset));
566 __ And(kScratchReg, kScratchReg,
567 Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
568 __ TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, ne, kScratchReg,
569 Operand(zero_reg));
570}

572// Assembles an instruction after register allocation, producing machine code.
573CodeGenerator::CodeGenResult CodeGenerator::AssembleArchInstruction(
574 Instruction* instr) {
575 MipsOperandConverter i(this, instr);
576 InstructionCode opcode = instr->opcode();
577 ArchOpcode arch_opcode = ArchOpcodeField::decode(opcode);
578 switch (arch_opcode) {
579 case kArchCallCodeObject: {
580 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
581 __ Call(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
582 } else {
583 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
584 CodeEntrypointTag tag =
585 i.InputCodeEntrypointTag(instr->CodeEnrypointTagInputIndex());
586 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
587 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
588 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
589 __ CallCodeObject(reg, tag);
590 }
591 RecordCallPosition(instr);
592 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
593 break;
594 }
595 case kArchCallBuiltinPointer: {
596 DCHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
597 Register builtin_index = i.InputRegister(0);
598 Register target =
599 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister)
600 ? kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister
601 : builtin_index;
602 __ CallBuiltinByIndex(builtin_index, target);
603 RecordCallPosition(instr);
604 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
605 break;
606 }
607#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
608 case kArchCallWasmFunction:
609 case kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect: {
610 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
611 DCHECK_EQ(arch_opcode, kArchCallWasmFunction);
612 Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
613 Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
614 __ Call(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
615 } else if (arch_opcode == kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect) {
616 __ CallWasmCodePointer(i.InputRegister(0));
617 } else {
618 __ Call(i.InputRegister(0));
619 }
620 RecordCallPosition(instr);
621 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
622 break;
623 }
624 case kArchTailCallWasm:
625 case kArchTailCallWasmIndirect: {
626 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
627 DCHECK_EQ(arch_opcode, kArchTailCallWasm);
628 Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
629 Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
630 __ Jump(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
631 } else if (arch_opcode == kArchTailCallWasmIndirect) {
632 __ CallWasmCodePointer(i.InputRegister(0), CallJumpMode::kTailCall);
633 } else {
634 __ Jump(i.InputRegister(0));
635 }
636 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
637 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
638 break;
639 }
640#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
641 case kArchTailCallCodeObject: {
642 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
643 __ Jump(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
644 } else {
645 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
646 CodeEntrypointTag tag =
647 i.InputCodeEntrypointTag(instr->CodeEnrypointTagInputIndex());
648 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
649 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
650 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
651 __ JumpCodeObject(reg, tag);
652 }
653 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
654 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
655 break;
656 }
657 case kArchTailCallAddress: {
658 CHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
659 Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
660 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
661 instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
662 reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
663 __ Jump(reg);
664 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
665 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
666 break;
667 }
668 case kArchCallJSFunction: {
669 Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
670 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
671 // Check the function's context matches the context argument.
672 __ Ld(kScratchReg, FieldMemOperand(func, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
673 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongFunctionContext, cp,
674 Operand(kScratchReg));
675 }
676 __ CallJSFunction(func);
677 RecordCallPosition(instr);
678 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
679 break;
680 }
681 case kArchPrepareCallCFunction: {
682 int const num_parameters = MiscField::decode(instr->opcode());
683 __ PrepareCallCFunction(num_parameters, kScratchReg);
684 // Frame alignment requires using FP-relative frame addressing.
685 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToFP();
686 break;
687 }
688 case kArchSaveCallerRegisters: {
689 fp_mode_ =
690 static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode()));
691 DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
692 fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
693 // kReturnRegister0 should have been saved before entering the stub.
694 int bytes = __ PushCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
695 DCHECK(IsAligned(bytes, kSystemPointerSize));
696 DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
697 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
698 DCHECK(!caller_registers_saved_);
699 caller_registers_saved_ = true;
700 break;
701 }
702 case kArchRestoreCallerRegisters: {
703 DCHECK(fp_mode_ ==
704 static_cast<SaveFPRegsMode>(MiscField::decode(instr->opcode())));
705 DCHECK(fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore ||
706 fp_mode_ == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave);
707 // Don't overwrite the returned value.
708 int bytes = __ PopCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
709 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-(bytes / kSystemPointerSize));
710 DCHECK_EQ(0, frame_access_state()->sp_delta());
711 DCHECK(caller_registers_saved_);
712 caller_registers_saved_ = false;
713 break;
714 }
715 case kArchPrepareTailCall:
716 AssemblePrepareTailCall();
717 break;
718 case kArchCallCFunctionWithFrameState:
719 case kArchCallCFunction: {
720 int const num_gp_parameters = ParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
721 int const num_fp_parameters = FPParamField::decode(instr->opcode());
722 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes;
723 Label return_location;
724#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
725 bool isWasmCapiFunction =
726 linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor()->IsWasmCapiFunction();
727 if (isWasmCapiFunction) {
728 // Put the return address in a stack slot.
729 __ LoadAddressPCRelative(kScratchReg, &return_location);
730 __ sd(kScratchReg,
731 MemOperand(fp, WasmExitFrameConstants::kCallingPCOffset));
732 set_isolate_data_slots = SetIsolateDataSlots::kNo;
733 }
734#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
735 int pc_offset;
736 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
737 ExternalReference ref = i.InputExternalReference(0);
738 pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(ref, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
739 set_isolate_data_slots, &return_location);
740 } else {
741 Register func = i.InputRegister(0);
742 pc_offset = __ CallCFunction(func, num_gp_parameters, num_fp_parameters,
743 set_isolate_data_slots, &return_location);
744 }
745 RecordSafepoint(instr->reference_map(), pc_offset);
746
747 bool const needs_frame_state =
748 (arch_opcode == kArchCallCFunctionWithFrameState);
749 if (needs_frame_state) {
750 RecordDeoptInfo(instr, pc_offset);
751 }
752
753 frame_access_state()->SetFrameAccessToDefault();
754 // Ideally, we should decrement SP delta to match the change of stack
755 // pointer in CallCFunction. However, for certain architectures (e.g.
756 // ARM), there may be more strict alignment requirement, causing old SP
757 // to be saved on the stack. In those cases, we can not calculate the SP
758 // delta statically.
759 frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
760 if (caller_registers_saved_) {
761 // Need to re-sync SP delta introduced in kArchSaveCallerRegisters.
762 // Here, we assume the sequence to be:
763 // kArchSaveCallerRegisters;
764 // kArchCallCFunction;
765 // kArchRestoreCallerRegisters;
766 int bytes =
767 __ RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(fp_mode_, kReturnRegister0);
768 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(bytes / kSystemPointerSize);
769 }
770 break;
771 }
772 case kArchJmp:
773 AssembleArchJump(i.InputRpo(0));
774 break;
775 case kArchBinarySearchSwitch:
776 AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitch(instr);
777 break;
778 case kArchTableSwitch:
779 AssembleArchTableSwitch(instr);
780 break;
781 case kArchAbortCSADcheck:
782 DCHECK(i.InputRegister(0) == a0);
783 {
784 // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
785 // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
786 FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
787 __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbortCSADcheck);
788 }
789 __ stop();
790 break;
791 case kArchDebugBreak:
792 __ DebugBreak();
793 break;
794 case kArchComment:
795 __ RecordComment(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(i.InputInt64(0)),
796 SourceLocation());
797 break;
798 case kArchNop:
799 case kArchThrowTerminator:

801 break;

811#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
812 case kArchStackPointer:

814 // we cannot use sp directly.

832 }

835 break;
836 case kArchFramePointer:

838 break;
839 case kArchParentFramePointer:

842 } else {
843 __ mov(i.OutputRegister(), fp);
844 }
845 break;
846 case kArchTruncateDoubleToI:
847 __ TruncateDoubleToI(isolate(), zone(), i.OutputRegister(),
848 i.InputDoubleRegister(0), DetermineStubCallMode());
849 break;
850 case kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier: // Fall through.
851 case kArchAtomicStoreWithWriteBarrier: {
852 RecordWriteMode mode = RecordWriteModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
853 Register object = i.InputRegister(0);
854 Register index = i.InputRegister(1);
855 Register value = i.InputRegister(2);
856 Register scratch0 = i.TempRegister(0);
857 Register scratch1 = i.TempRegister(1);
858 auto ool = zone()->New<OutOfLineRecordWrite>(this, object, index, value,
859 scratch0, scratch1, mode,
860 DetermineStubCallMode());
861 __ Daddu(kScratchReg, object, index);
862 if (arch_opcode == kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier) {
863 __ Sd(value, MemOperand(kScratchReg));
864 } else {
865 DCHECK_EQ(kArchAtomicStoreWithWriteBarrier, arch_opcode);
866 __ sync();
867 __ Sd(value, MemOperand(kScratchReg));
868 __ sync();
869 }
870 if (mode > RecordWriteMode::kValueIsPointer) {
871 __ JumpIfSmi(value, ool->exit());
872 }
873 __ CheckPageFlag(object, scratch0,
874 MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, ne,
875 ool->entry());
876 __ bind(ool->exit());
877 break;
878 }
879 case kArchStoreIndirectWithWriteBarrier:
880 UNREACHABLE();
881 case kArchStackSlot: {
882 FrameOffset offset =
883 frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(i.InputInt32(0));
884 Register base_reg = offset.from_stack_pointer() ? sp : fp;
885 __ Daddu(i.OutputRegister(), base_reg, Operand(offset.offset()));
886 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
887 // Verify that the output_register is properly aligned
888 __ And(kScratchReg, i.OutputRegister(),
889 Operand(kSystemPointerSize - 1));
890 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kAllocationIsNotDoubleAligned, kScratchReg,
891 Operand(zero_reg));
892 }
893 break;

1234 case kMips64CmpS: {
1235 FPURegister left = i.InputOrZeroSingleRegister(0);

1238 FPUCondition cc =
1239 FlagsConditionToConditionCmpFPU(&predicate, instr->flags_condition());
1240
1241 if ((left == kDoubleRegZero || right == kDoubleRegZero) &&
1242 !__ IsDoubleZeroRegSet()) {
1243 __ Move(kDoubleRegZero, 0.0);
1244 }
1245
1246 __ CompareF32(cc, left, right);
1247 } break;
1248 case kMips64AddS:
1249 // TODO(plind): add special case: combine mult & add.
1250 __ add_s(i.OutputDoubleRegister(), i.InputDoubleRegister(0),
1251 i.InputDoubleRegister(1));
1252 break;

1255 i.InputDoubleRegister(1));
1256 break;

1261 break;

1264 i.InputDoubleRegister(1));
1265 break;

1268 __ abs_s(i.OutputSingleRegister(), i.InputSingleRegister(0));
1269 } else {
1270 __ mfc1(kScratchReg, i.InputSingleRegister(0));
1271 __ Dins(kScratchReg, zero_reg, 31, 1);
1272 __ mtc1(kScratchReg, i.OutputSingleRegister());
1273 }
1274 break;
1275 case kMips64NegS:
1276 __ Neg_s(i.OutputSingleRegister(), i.InputSingleRegister(0));
1277 break;

1280 break;

1284 i.InputDoubleRegister(1));

1286 case kMips64MinS:
1287 __ min_s(i.OutputDoubleRegister(), i.InputDoubleRegister(0),
1288 i.InputDoubleRegister(1));
1289 break;
1290 case kMips64CmpD: {
1291 FPURegister left = i.InputOrZeroDoubleRegister(0);
1292 FPURegister right = i.InputOrZeroDoubleRegister(1);
1293 bool predicate;
1294 FPUCondition cc =
1295 FlagsConditionToConditionCmpFPU(&predicate, instr->flags_condition());
1296 if ((left == kDoubleRegZero || right == kDoubleRegZero) &&
1297 !__ IsDoubleZeroRegSet()) {
1298 __ Move(kDoubleRegZero, 0.0);
1299 }
1300 __ CompareF64(cc, left, right);
1301 } break;

1543

1545 // Other arches use round to zero here, so we follow.

1552 (kFCSROverflowCauseMask | kFCSRInvalidOpCauseMask));
1553 __ Slt(result, zero_reg, result);

1582 __ slt(kScratchReg2, kScratchReg, i.OutputRegister());

1792 case kMips64Push:
1793 if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsFPRegister()) {
1794 __ Sdc1(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), MemOperand(sp, -kDoubleSize));
1795 __ Subu(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleSize));
1796 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize);
1797 } else {
1798 __ Push(i.InputRegister(0));
1799 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(1);
1800 }

1802 case kMips64Peek: {
1803 int reverse_slot = i.InputInt32(0);
1804 int offset =
1805 FrameSlotToFPOffset(frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - reverse_slot);
1806 if (instr->OutputAt(0)->IsFPRegister()) {
1807 LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(instr->OutputAt(0));
1808 if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
1809 __ Ldc1(i.OutputDoubleRegister(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1810 } else if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1811 __ Lwc1(
1812 i.OutputSingleRegister(0),
1813 MemOperand(fp, offset + kLessSignificantWordInDoublewordOffset));
1814 } else {
1815 DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, op->representation());
1816 __ ld_b(i.OutputSimd128Register(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1817 }
1818 } else {
1819 __ Ld(i.OutputRegister(0), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1820 }
1821 break;

2063#define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(op, inst32, inst64) \
2064 case kAtomic##op##Int8: \
2065 DCHECK_EQ(AtomicWidthField::decode(opcode), AtomicWidth::kWord32); \
2066 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll, Sc, true, 8, inst32, 32); \
2067 break; \
2068 case kAtomic##op##Uint8: \
2069 switch (AtomicWidthField::decode(opcode)) { \
2070 case AtomicWidth::kWord32: \
2071 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll, Sc, false, 8, inst32, 32); \
2072 break; \
2073 case AtomicWidth::kWord64: \
2074 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Lld, Scd, false, 8, inst64, 64); \
2075 break; \
2076 } \
2077 break; \
2078 case kAtomic##op##Int16: \
2079 DCHECK_EQ(AtomicWidthField::decode(opcode), AtomicWidth::kWord32); \
2080 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll, Sc, true, 16, inst32, 32); \
2081 break; \
2082 case kAtomic##op##Uint16: \
2083 switch (AtomicWidthField::decode(opcode)) { \
2084 case AtomicWidth::kWord32: \
2085 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Ll, Sc, false, 16, inst32, 32); \
2086 break; \
2087 case AtomicWidth::kWord64: \
2088 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Lld, Scd, false, 16, inst64, 64); \
2089 break; \
2090 } \
2091 break; \
2092 case kAtomic##op##Word32: \
2093 switch (AtomicWidthField::decode(opcode)) { \
2094 case AtomicWidth::kWord32: \
2095 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(Ll, Sc, inst32); \
2096 break; \
2097 case AtomicWidth::kWord64: \
2098 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP_EXT(Lld, Scd, false, 32, inst64, 64); \
2099 break; \
2100 } \
2101 break; \
2102 case kMips64Word64Atomic##op##Uint64: \
2103 ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(Lld, Scd, inst64); \
2104 break;
2105 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Add, Addu, Daddu)
2106 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Sub, Subu, Dsubu)
2107 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(And, And, And)
2108 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Or, Or, Or)
2109 ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Xor, Xor, Xor)
2110#undef ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE

2206 case kMips64F64x2Min: {
2207 CpuFeatureScope msa_scope(masm(), MIPS_SIMD);
2208 Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register();
2209 Simd128Register src0 = i.InputSimd128Register(0);
2210 Simd128Register src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
2211 Simd128Register scratch0 = kSimd128RegZero;
2212 Simd128Register scratch1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
2213
2214 // If inputs are -0.0. and +0.0, then write -0.0 to scratch1.
2215 // scratch1 = (src0 == src1) ? (src0 | src1) : (src1 | src1).
2216 __ fseq_d(scratch0, src0, src1);
2217 __ bsel_v(scratch0, src1, src0);
2218 __ or_v(scratch1, scratch0, src1);
2219 // scratch0 = isNaN(src0) ? src0 : scratch1.
2220 __ fseq_d(scratch0, src0, src0);
2221 __ bsel_v(scratch0, src0, scratch1);
2222 // scratch1 = (src0 < scratch0) ? src0 : scratch0.
2223 __ fslt_d(scratch1, src0, scratch0);
2224 __ bsel_v(scratch1, scratch0, src0);
2225 // Canonicalize the result.
2226 __ fmin_d(dst, scratch1, scratch1);
2227 break;

2234 Simd128Register scratch0 = kSimd128RegZero;
2235 Simd128Register scratch1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;

2237 // If inputs are -0.0. and +0.0, then write +0.0 to scratch1.

2240 __ bsel_v(scratch0, src1, src0);
2241 __ and_v(scratch1, scratch0, src1);
2242 // scratch0 = isNaN(src0) ? src0 : scratch1.
2243 __ fseq_d(scratch0, src0, src0);
2244 __ bsel_v(scratch0, src0, scratch1);
2245 // scratch1 = (scratch0 < src0) ? src0 : scratch0.
2246 __ fslt_d(scratch1, scratch0, src0);

3479 case kMips64S32x4Shuffle: {
3480 CpuFeatureScope msa_scope(masm(), MIPS_SIMD);
3481 Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register(),
3482 src0 = i.InputSimd128Register(0),
3483 src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
3484
3485 int32_t shuffle = i.InputInt32(2);
3486
3487 if (src0 == src1) {
3488 // Unary S32x4 shuffles are handled with shf.w instruction
3489 unsigned lane = shuffle & 0xFF;
3490 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3491 // range of all four lanes, for unary instruction,
3492 // should belong to the same range, which can be one of these:
3493 // [0, 3] or [4, 7]
3494 if (lane >= 4) {
3495 int32_t shuffle_helper = shuffle;
3496 for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
3497 lane = shuffle_helper & 0xFF;
3498 CHECK_GE(lane, 4);
3499 shuffle_helper >>= 8;
3500 }
3501 }
3502 }
3503 uint32_t i8 = 0;
3504 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3505 lane = shuffle & 0xFF;
3506 if (lane >= 4) {
3507 lane -= 4;
3508 }
3509 DCHECK_GT(4, lane);
3510 i8 |= lane << (2 * i);
3511 shuffle >>= 8;
3512 }
3513 __ shf_w(dst, src0, i8);
3514 } else {
3515 // For binary shuffles use vshf.w instruction
3516 if (dst == src0) {
3517 __ move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, src0);
3518 src0 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
3519 } else if (dst == src1) {
3520 __ move_v(kSimd128ScratchReg, src1);
3521 src1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
3522 }
3523
3524 __ li(kScratchReg, i.InputInt32(2));
3525 __ insert_w(dst, 0, kScratchReg);
3526 __ xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
3527 __ ilvr_b(dst, kSimd128RegZero, dst);
3528 __ ilvr_h(dst, kSimd128RegZero, dst);
3529 __ vshf_w(dst, src1, src0);
3530 }
3531 break;
3532 }

3689 static_cast<int64_t>(i.InputInt32(3)) << 32 | i.InputInt32(2);

3691 static_cast<int64_t>(i.InputInt32(5)) << 32 | i.InputInt32(4);

3830 }
3831 case kMips64I8x16UConvertI16x8: {
3832 CpuFeatureScope msa_scope(masm(), MIPS_SIMD);
3833 Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register();
3834 Simd128Register src0 = i.InputSimd128Register(0);
3835 Simd128Register src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
3836 __ xor_v(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
3837 __ max_s_h(kSimd128ScratchReg, kSimd128RegZero, src0);
3838 __ sat_u_h(kSimd128ScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg, 7);
3839 __ max_s_h(dst, kSimd128RegZero, src1);
3840 __ sat_u_h(dst, dst, 7);
3841 __ pckev_b(dst, dst, kSimd128ScratchReg);
3842 break;
3843 }
3844 }
3845 return kSuccess;
3846}
3847
3848#define UNSUPPORTED_COND(opcode, condition) \
3849 StdoutStream{} << "Unsupported " << #opcode << " condition: \"" << condition \
3850 << "\""; \
3851 UNIMPLEMENTED();
3852
3853void AssembleBranchToLabels(CodeGenerator* gen, MacroAssembler* masm,
3854 Instruction* instr, FlagsCondition condition,
3855 Label* tlabel, Label* flabel, bool fallthru) {
3856#undef __
3857#define __ masm->
3858 MipsOperandConverter i(gen, instr);
3859
3860 // MIPS does not have condition code flags, so compare and branch are
3861 // implemented differently than on the other arch's. The compare operations
3862 // emit mips pseudo-instructions, which are handled here by branch
3863 // instructions that do the actual comparison. Essential that the input
3864 // registers to compare pseudo-op are not modified before this branch op, as
3865 // they are tested here.
3866
3867 if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Tst) {
3868 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionTst(condition);
3869 __ Branch(tlabel, cc, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
3870 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Dadd ||
3871 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Dsub) {
3872 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionOvf(condition);
3873 __ dsra32(kScratchReg, i.OutputRegister(), 0);
3874 __ sra(kScratchReg2, i.OutputRegister(), 31);
3875 __ Branch(tlabel, cc, kScratchReg2, Operand(kScratchReg));
3876 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64DaddOvf ||
3877 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64DsubOvf) {
3878 switch (condition) {
3879 // Overflow occurs if overflow register is negative
3880 case kOverflow:
3881 __ Branch(tlabel, lt, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
3882 break;
3883 case kNotOverflow:
3884 __ Branch(tlabel, ge, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
3885 break;
3886 default:
3887 UNSUPPORTED_COND(instr->arch_opcode(), condition);
3888 }
3889 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64MulOvf ||
3890 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64DMulOvf) {
3891 // Overflow occurs if overflow register is not zero
3892 switch (condition) {
3893 case kOverflow:
3894 __ Branch(tlabel, ne, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
3895 break;
3896 case kNotOverflow:
3897 __ Branch(tlabel, eq, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
3898 break;
3899 default:
3900 UNSUPPORTED_COND(instr->arch_opcode(), condition);
3901 }
3902 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Cmp) {
3903 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionCmp(condition);
3904 __ Branch(tlabel, cc, i.InputRegister(0), i.InputOperand(1));
3905 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kArchStackPointerGreaterThan) {
3906 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionCmp(condition);
3907 DCHECK((cc == ls) || (cc == hi));
3908 if (cc == ls) {
3909 __ xori(i.TempRegister(0), i.TempRegister(0), 1);
3910 }
3911 __ Branch(tlabel, ne, i.TempRegister(0), Operand(zero_reg));
3912 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64CmpS ||
3913 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64CmpD) {
3914 bool predicate;
3915 FlagsConditionToConditionCmpFPU(&predicate, condition);
3916 if (predicate) {
3917 __ BranchTrueF(tlabel);
3918 } else {
3919 __ BranchFalseF(tlabel);
3920 }
3921 } else {
3922 PrintF("AssembleArchBranch Unimplemented arch_opcode: %d\n",
3923 instr->arch_opcode());
3924 UNIMPLEMENTED();
3925 }
3926 if (!fallthru) __ Branch(flabel); // no fallthru to flabel.
3927#undef __
3928#define __ masm()->
3929}
3930
3931// Assembles branches after an instruction.
3932void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBranch(Instruction* instr, BranchInfo* branch) {
3933 Label* tlabel = branch->true_label;
3934 Label* flabel = branch->false_label;
3935
3936 AssembleBranchToLabels(this, masm(), instr, branch->condition, tlabel, flabel,
3937 branch->fallthru);
3938}
3939
3940#undef UNSUPPORTED_COND

3942void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchDeoptBranch(Instruction* instr,
3943 BranchInfo* branch) {
3944 AssembleArchBranch(instr, branch);
3945}

3952#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3953void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchTrap(Instruction* instr,
3954 FlagsCondition condition) {
3955 class OutOfLineTrap final : public OutOfLineCode {
3956 public:
3957 OutOfLineTrap(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
3958 : OutOfLineCode(gen), instr_(instr), gen_(gen) {}
3959 void Generate() final {
3960 MipsOperandConverter i(gen_, instr_);
3961 TrapId trap_id =
3962 static_cast<TrapId>(i.InputInt32(instr_->InputCount() - 1));
3963 GenerateCallToTrap(trap_id);
3964 }
3965
3966 private:
3967 void GenerateCallToTrap(TrapId trap_id) {
3968 gen_->AssembleSourcePosition(instr_);
3969 // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
3970 // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched when the code
3971 // is added to the native module and copied into wasm code space.
3972 __ Call(static_cast<Address>(trap_id), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
3973 ReferenceMap* reference_map =
3974 gen_->zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(gen_->zone());
3975 gen_->RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
3976 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3977 __ stop();
3978 }
3979 }
3980 Instruction* instr_;
3981 CodeGenerator* gen_;
3982 };
3983 auto ool = zone()->New<OutOfLineTrap>(this, instr);
3984 Label* tlabel = ool->entry();
3985 AssembleBranchToLabels(this, masm(), instr, condition, tlabel, nullptr, true);
3986}
3987#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

3989// Assembles boolean materializations after an instruction.
3990void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBoolean(Instruction* instr,
3991 FlagsCondition condition) {
3992 MipsOperandConverter i(this, instr);
3993
3994 // Materialize a full 32-bit 1 or 0 value. The result register is always the
3995 // last output of the instruction.
3996 DCHECK_NE(0u, instr->OutputCount());
3997 Register result = i.OutputRegister(instr->OutputCount() - 1);
3998 // MIPS does not have condition code flags, so compare and branch are
3999 // implemented differently than on the other arch's. The compare operations
4000 // emit mips pseudo-instructions, which are checked and handled here.
4001
4002 if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Tst) {
4003 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionTst(condition);
4004 if (cc == eq) {
4005 __ Sltu(result, kScratchReg, 1);
4006 } else {
4007 __ Sltu(result, zero_reg, kScratchReg);
4008 }
4009 return;
4010 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Dadd ||
4011 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Dsub) {
4012 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionOvf(condition);
4013 // Check for overflow creates 1 or 0 for result.
4014 __ dsrl32(kScratchReg, i.OutputRegister(), 31);
4015 __ srl(kScratchReg2, i.OutputRegister(), 31);
4016 __ xor_(result, kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
4017 if (cc == eq) // Toggle result for not overflow.
4018 __ xori(result, result, 1);
4019 return;
4020 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64DaddOvf ||
4021 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64DsubOvf) {
4022 // Overflow occurs if overflow register is negative
4023 __ slt(result, kScratchReg, zero_reg);
4024 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64MulOvf ||
4025 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64DMulOvf) {
4026 // Overflow occurs if overflow register is not zero
4027 __ Sgtu(result, kScratchReg, zero_reg);
4028 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64Cmp) {
4029 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionCmp(condition);
4030 __ CompareWord(cc, result, i.InputRegister(0), i.InputOperand(1));
4031 return;
4032 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64CmpD ||
4033 instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64CmpS) {
4034 FPURegister left = i.InputOrZeroDoubleRegister(0);
4035 FPURegister right = i.InputOrZeroDoubleRegister(1);
4036 if ((left == kDoubleRegZero || right == kDoubleRegZero) &&
4037 !__ IsDoubleZeroRegSet()) {
4038 __ Move(kDoubleRegZero, 0.0);
4039 }
4040 bool predicate;
4041 FlagsConditionToConditionCmpFPU(&predicate, condition);
4042 if (kArchVariant != kMips64r6) {
4043 __ li(result, Operand(1));
4044 if (predicate) {
4045 __ Movf(result, zero_reg);
4046 } else {
4047 __ Movt(result, zero_reg);
4048 }
4049 } else {
4050 if (instr->arch_opcode() == kMips64CmpD) {
4051 __ dmfc1(result, kDoubleCompareReg);
4052 } else {
4053 DCHECK_EQ(kMips64CmpS, instr->arch_opcode());
4054 __ mfc1(result, kDoubleCompareReg);
4055 }
4056 if (predicate) {
4057 __ And(result, result, 1); // cmp returns all 1's/0's, use only LSB.
4058 } else {
4059 __ Addu(result, result, 1); // Toggle result for not equal.
4060 }
4061 }
4062 return;
4063 } else if (instr->arch_opcode() == kArchStackPointerGreaterThan) {
4064 Condition cc = FlagsConditionToConditionCmp(condition);
4065 DCHECK((cc == ls) || (cc == hi));
4066 if (cc == ls) {
4067 __ xori(i.OutputRegister(), i.TempRegister(0), 1);
4068 }
4069 return;
4070 } else {
4071 PrintF("AssembleArchBranch Unimplemented arch_opcode is : %d\n",
4072 instr->arch_opcode());
4073 TRACE("UNIMPLEMENTED code_generator_mips: %s at line %d\n", __FUNCTION__,
4074 __LINE__);
4075 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4076 }
4077}

4088void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitch(Instruction* instr) {
4089 MipsOperandConverter i(this, instr);
4090 Register input = i.InputRegister(0);
4091 std::vector<std::pair<int32_t, Label*>> cases;
4092 for (size_t index = 2; index < instr->InputCount(); index += 2) {
4093 cases.push_back({i.InputInt32(index + 0), GetLabel(i.InputRpo(index + 1))});
4094 }
4095
4096 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4097 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4098 // The input register may contains dirty data in upper 32 bits, explicitly
4099 // sign-extend it here.
4100 __ sll(scratch, input, 0);
4101 AssembleArchBinarySearchSwitchRange(scratch, i.InputRpo(1), cases.data(),
4102 cases.data() + cases.size());
4103}
4104
4105void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchTableSwitch(Instruction* instr) {
4106 MipsOperandConverter i(this, instr);
4107 Register input = i.InputRegister(0);
4108 size_t const case_count = instr->InputCount() - 2;
4109
4110 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4111 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4112 // The input register may contains dirty data in upper 32 bits, explicitly
4113 // sign-extend it here.
4114 __ sll(scratch, input, 0);
4115 __ Branch(GetLabel(i.InputRpo(1)), hs, scratch, Operand(case_count));
4116 __ GenerateSwitchTable(scratch, case_count, [&i, this](size_t index) {
4117 return GetLabel(i.InputRpo(index + 2));
4118 });
4119}

4126void CodeGenerator::FinishFrame(Frame* frame) {
4127 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
4128
4129 const DoubleRegList saves_fpu = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
4130 if (!saves_fpu.is_empty()) {
4131 int count = saves_fpu.Count();
4132 DCHECK_EQ(kNumCalleeSavedFPU, count);
4133 frame->AllocateSavedCalleeRegisterSlots(count *
4134 (kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize));
4135 }
4136
4137 const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
4138 if (!saves.is_empty()) {
4139 int count = saves.Count();
4140 frame->AllocateSavedCalleeRegisterSlots(count);
4141 }
4142}
4143
4144void CodeGenerator::AssembleConstructFrame() {
4145 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
4146
4147 if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
4148 if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
4149#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4150 if (info()->GetOutputStackFrameType() == StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY) {
4151 __ StubPrologue(StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY);
4152 // Reserve stack space for saving the c_entry_fp later.
4153 __ Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
4154#else
4155 // For balance.
4156 if (false) {
4157#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4158 } else {
4159 __ Push(ra, fp);
4160 __ mov(fp, sp);
4161 }
4162 } else if (call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall()) {
4163 __ Prologue();
4164 } else {
4165 __ StubPrologue(info()->GetOutputStackFrameType());
4166#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4167 if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() ||
4168 call_descriptor->IsWasmImportWrapper() ||
4169 call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
4170 // For import wrappers and C-API functions, this stack slot is only used
4171 // for printing stack traces in V8. Also, it holds a WasmImportData
4172 // instead of the trusted instance data, which is taken care of in the
4173 // frames accessors.
4174 __ Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
4175 }
4176 if (call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
4177 // Reserve space for saving the PC later.
4178 __ Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
4179 }
4180#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4181 }
4182 }
4183
4184 int required_slots =
4185 frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - frame()->GetFixedSlotCount();
4186
4187 if (info()->is_osr()) {
4188 // TurboFan OSR-compiled functions cannot be entered directly.
4189 __ Abort(AbortReason::kShouldNotDirectlyEnterOsrFunction);
4190
4191 // Unoptimized code jumps directly to this entrypoint while the unoptimized
4192 // frame is still on the stack. Optimized code uses OSR values directly from
4193 // the unoptimized frame. Thus, all that needs to be done is to allocate the
4194 // remaining stack slots.
4195 __ RecordComment("-- OSR entrypoint --");
4196 osr_pc_offset_ = __ pc_offset();
4197 required_slots -= osr_helper()->UnoptimizedFrameSlots();
4198 }
4199
4200 const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
4201 const DoubleRegList saves_fpu = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
4202
4203 if (required_slots > 0) {
4204 DCHECK(frame_access_state()->has_frame());
4205#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4206 if (info()->IsWasm() && required_slots * kSystemPointerSize > 4 * KB) {
4207 // For WebAssembly functions with big frames we have to do the stack
4208 // overflow check before we construct the frame. Otherwise we may not
4209 // have enough space on the stack to call the runtime for the stack
4210 // overflow.
4211 Label done;
4212
4213 // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
4214 // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
4215 // check in the condition code.
4216 if (required_slots * kSystemPointerSize < v8_flags.stack_size * KB) {
4217 __ LoadStackLimit(kScratchReg,
4218 MacroAssembler::StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
4219 __ Daddu(kScratchReg, kScratchReg,
4220 Operand(required_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4221 __ Branch(&done, uge, sp, Operand(kScratchReg));
4222 }
4223
4224 __ Call(static_cast<intptr_t>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
4225 RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
4226 // The call does not return, hence we can ignore any references and just
4227 // define an empty safepoint.
4228 ReferenceMap* reference_map = zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(zone());
4229 RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
4230 if (v8_flags.debug_code) __ stop();
4231
4232 __ bind(&done);
4233 }
4234#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4235 }
4236
4237 const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
4238
4239 // Skip callee-saved and return slots, which are pushed below.
4240 required_slots -= saves.Count();
4241 required_slots -= saves_fpu.Count();
4242 required_slots -= returns;
4243 if (required_slots > 0) {
4244 __ Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(required_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4245 }
4246
4247 if (!saves_fpu.is_empty()) {
4248 // Save callee-saved FPU registers.
4249 __ MultiPushFPU(saves_fpu);
4250 DCHECK_EQ(kNumCalleeSavedFPU, saves_fpu.Count());
4251 }
4252
4253 if (!saves.is_empty()) {
4254 // Save callee-saved registers.
4255 __ MultiPush(saves);
4256 }
4257
4258 if (returns != 0) {
4259 // Create space for returns.
4260 __ Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(returns * kSystemPointerSize));
4261 }
4262
4263 for (int spill_slot : frame()->tagged_slots()) {
4264 FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(spill_slot);
4265 DCHECK(offset.from_frame_pointer());
4266 __ Sd(zero_reg, MemOperand(fp, offset.offset()));
4267 }
4268}
4269
4270void CodeGenerator::AssembleReturn(InstructionOperand* additional_pop_count) {
4271 auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
4272
4273 const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
4274 if (returns != 0) {
4275 __ Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(returns * kSystemPointerSize));
4276 }
4277
4278 // Restore GP registers.
4279 const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
4280 if (!saves.is_empty()) {
4281 __ MultiPop(saves);
4282 }
4283
4284 // Restore FPU registers.
4285 const DoubleRegList saves_fpu = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
4286 if (!saves_fpu.is_empty()) {
4287 __ MultiPopFPU(saves_fpu);
4288 }
4289
4290 MipsOperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4291
4292 const int parameter_slots =
4293 static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount());
4294
4295 // {aditional_pop_count} is only greater than zero if {parameter_slots = 0}.
4296 // Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
4297 if (parameter_slots != 0) {
4298 if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
4299 DCHECK_EQ(g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32(), 0);
4300 } else if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4301 __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedAdditionalPopValue,
4302 g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count),
4303 Operand(static_cast<int64_t>(0)));
4304 }
4305 }
4306
4307 // Functions with JS linkage have at least one parameter (the receiver).
4308 // If {parameter_slots} == 0, it means it is a builtin with
4309 // kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel, which takes care of JS arguments popping
4310 // itself.
4311 const bool drop_jsargs = frame_access_state()->has_frame() &&
4312 call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall() &&
4313 parameter_slots != 0;
4314
4315 if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
4316 AssembleDeconstructFrame();
4317 } else if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
4318 // Canonicalize JSFunction return sites for now unless they have an variable
4319 // number of stack slot pops.
4320 if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate() &&
4321 g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32() == 0) {
4322 if (return_label_.is_bound()) {
4323 __ Branch(&return_label_);
4324 return;
4325 } else {
4326 __ bind(&return_label_);
4327 }
4328 }
4329 if (drop_jsargs) {
4330 // Get the actual argument count
4331 __ Ld(t0, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
4332 }
4333 AssembleDeconstructFrame();
4334 }
4335 if (drop_jsargs) {
4336 // We must pop all arguments from the stack (including the receiver). This
4337 // number of arguments is given by max(1 + argc_reg, parameter_slots).
4338 if (parameter_slots > 1) {
4339 __ li(kScratchReg, parameter_slots);
4340 __ slt(kScratchReg2, t0, kScratchReg);
4341 __ movn(t0, kScratchReg, kScratchReg2);
4342 }
4343 __ Dlsa(sp, sp, t0, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
4344 } else if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
4345 int additional_count = g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32();
4346 __ Drop(parameter_slots + additional_count);
4347 } else {
4348 Register pop_reg = g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count);
4349 __ Drop(parameter_slots);
4350 __ Dlsa(sp, sp, pop_reg, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
4351 }
4352 __ Ret();
4353}

4355void CodeGenerator::FinishCode() {}

4357void CodeGenerator::PrepareForDeoptimizationExits(
4358 ZoneDeque<DeoptimizationExit*>* exits) {}
4359
4360AllocatedOperand CodeGenerator::Push(InstructionOperand* source) {
4361 auto rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
4362 int new_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
4363 MipsOperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4364 int last_frame_slot_id =
4365 frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
4366 int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
4367 int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta + new_slots;
4368 AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
4369 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4370 __ Push(g.ToRegister(source));
4371 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4372 } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
4373 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4374 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4375 __ Ld(scratch, g.ToMemOperand(source));
4376 __ Push(scratch);
4377 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4378 } else {
4379 // No push instruction for this operand type. Bump the stack pointer and
4380 // assemble the move.
4381 __ Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(new_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4382 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
4383 AssembleMove(source, &stack_slot);
4384 }
4385 temp_slots_ += new_slots;
4386 return stack_slot;
4387}
4388
4389void CodeGenerator::Pop(InstructionOperand* dest, MachineRepresentation rep) {
4390 MipsOperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4391 int dropped_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
4392 if (dest->IsRegister()) {
4393 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4394 __ Pop(g.ToRegister(dest));
4395 } else if (dest->IsStackSlot()) {
4396 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4397 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4398 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4399 __ Pop(scratch);
4400 __ Sd(scratch, g.ToMemOperand(dest));
4401 } else {
4402 int last_frame_slot_id =
4403 frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
4404 int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
4405 int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta;
4406 AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
4407 AssembleMove(&stack_slot, dest);
4408 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
4409 __ Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(dropped_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
4410 }
4411 temp_slots_ -= dropped_slots;
4412}
4413
4414void CodeGenerator::PopTempStackSlots() {
4415 if (temp_slots_ > 0) {
4416 frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-temp_slots_);
4417 __ Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(temp_slots_ * kSystemPointerSize));
4418 temp_slots_ = 0;
4419 }
4420}
4421
4422void CodeGenerator::MoveToTempLocation(InstructionOperand* source,
4423 MachineRepresentation rep) {
4424 // Must be kept in sync with {MoveTempLocationTo}.
4425 DCHECK(!source->IsImmediate());
4426 move_cycle_.temps.emplace(masm());
4427 auto& temps = *move_cycle_.temps;
4428 // Temporarily exclude the reserved scratch registers while we pick one to
4429 // resolve the move cycle. Re-include them immediately afterwards as they
4430 // might be needed for the move to the temp location.
4431 temps.Exclude(move_cycle_.scratch_regs);
4432 if (!IsFloatingPoint(rep)) {
4433 if (temps.hasAvailable()) {
4434 Register scratch = move_cycle_.temps->Acquire();
4435 move_cycle_.scratch_reg.emplace(scratch);
4436 }
4437 }
4438
4439 temps.Include(move_cycle_.scratch_regs);
4440
4441 if (move_cycle_.scratch_reg.has_value()) {
4442 // A scratch register is available for this rep.
4443 // auto& scratch_reg = *move_cycle_.scratch_reg;
4444 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep,
4445 move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4446 AssembleMove(source, &scratch);
4447 } else {
4448 // The scratch registers are blocked by pending moves. Use the stack
4449 // instead.
4450 Push(source);
4451 }
4452}
4453
4454void CodeGenerator::MoveTempLocationTo(InstructionOperand* dest,
4455 MachineRepresentation rep) {
4456 if (move_cycle_.scratch_reg.has_value()) {
4457 // auto& scratch_reg = *move_cycle_.scratch_reg;
4458 AllocatedOperand scratch(LocationOperand::REGISTER, rep,
4459 move_cycle_.scratch_reg->code());
4460 AssembleMove(&scratch, dest);
4461 } else {
4462 Pop(dest, rep);
4463 }
4464 // Restore the default state to release the {UseScratchRegisterScope} and to
4465 // prepare for the next cycle.
4466 move_cycle_ = MoveCycleState();
4467}
4468
4469void CodeGenerator::SetPendingMove(MoveOperands* move) {
4470 InstructionOperand* src = &move->source();
4471 InstructionOperand* dst = &move->destination();
4472 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
4473 if (src->IsConstant() && dst->IsFPLocationOperand()) {
4474 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
4475 move_cycle_.scratch_regs.set(temp);
4476 } else if (src->IsAnyStackSlot() || dst->IsAnyStackSlot()) {
4477 MipsOperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4478 bool src_need_scratch = false;
4479 bool dst_need_scratch = false;
4480 if (src->IsAnyStackSlot()) {
4481 MemOperand src_mem = g.ToMemOperand(src);
4482 src_need_scratch =
4483 (!is_int16(src_mem.offset())) || (((src_mem.offset() & 0b111) != 0) &&
4484 !is_int16(src_mem.offset() + 4));
4485 }
4486 if (dst->IsAnyStackSlot()) {
4487 MemOperand dst_mem = g.ToMemOperand(dst);
4488 dst_need_scratch =
4489 (!is_int16(dst_mem.offset())) || (((dst_mem.offset() & 0b111) != 0) &&
4490 !is_int16(dst_mem.offset() + 4));
4491 }
4492 if (src_need_scratch || dst_need_scratch) {
4493 Register temp = temps.Acquire();
4494 move_cycle_.scratch_regs.set(temp);
4495 }
4496 }
4497}

4501bool Is32BitOperand(InstructionOperand* operand) {
4502 DCHECK(operand->IsStackSlot() || operand->IsRegister());
4503 MachineRepresentation mr = LocationOperand::cast(operand)->representation();
4504 return mr == MachineRepresentation::kWord32 ||
4505 mr == MachineRepresentation::kCompressed ||
4506 mr == MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer;
4507}
4508
4509// When we need only 32 bits, move only 32 bits, otherwise the destination
4510// register' upper 32 bits may contain dirty data.
4511bool Use32BitMove(InstructionOperand* source, InstructionOperand* destination) {
4512 return Is32BitOperand(source) && Is32BitOperand(destination);
4513}
4514
4515} // namespace
4516
4517void CodeGenerator::AssembleMove(InstructionOperand* source,
4518 InstructionOperand* destination) {
4519 MipsOperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4520 // Dispatch on the source and destination operand kinds. Not all
4521 // combinations are possible.
4522 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4523 DCHECK(destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot());
4524 Register src = g.ToRegister(source);
4525 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
4526 __ mov(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
4527 } else {
4528 __ Sd(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4529 }
4530 } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
4531 DCHECK(destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot());
4532 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source);
4533 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
4534 if (Use32BitMove(source, destination)) {
4535 __ Lw(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
4536 } else {
4537 __ Ld(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
4538 }
4539 } else {
4540 Register temp = kScratchReg;
4541 __ Ld(temp, src);
4542 __ Sd(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4543 }
4544 } else if (source->IsConstant()) {
4545 Constant src = g.ToConstant(source);
4546 if (destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot()) {
4547 Register dst =
4548 destination->IsRegister() ? g.ToRegister(destination) : kScratchReg;
4549 switch (src.type()) {
4550 case Constant::kInt32:
4551 __ li(dst, Operand(src.ToInt32(), src.rmode()));
4552 break;
4553 case Constant::kFloat32:
4554 __ li(dst, Operand::EmbeddedNumber(src.ToFloat32()));
4555 break;
4556 case Constant::kInt64:
4557 __ li(dst, Operand(src.ToInt64(), src.rmode()));
4558 break;
4559 case Constant::kFloat64:
4560 __ li(dst, Operand::EmbeddedNumber(src.ToFloat64().value()));
4561 break;
4562 case Constant::kExternalReference:
4563 __ li(dst, src.ToExternalReference());
4564 break;
4565 case Constant::kHeapObject: {
4566 Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
4567 RootIndex index;
4568 if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
4569 __ LoadRoot(dst, index);
4570 } else {
4571 __ li(dst, src_object);
4572 }
4573 break;
4574 }
4575 case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject:
4576 UNREACHABLE();
4577 case Constant::kRpoNumber:
4578 UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(titzer): loading RPO numbers on mips64.
4579 }
4580 if (destination->IsStackSlot()) __ Sd(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4581 } else if (src.type() == Constant::kFloat32) {
4582 if (destination->IsFPStackSlot()) {
4583 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination);
4584 if (base::bit_cast<int32_t>(src.ToFloat32()) == 0) {
4585 __ Sd(zero_reg, dst);
4586 } else {
4587 __ li(kScratchReg, Operand(base::bit_cast<int32_t>(src.ToFloat32())));
4588 __ Sd(kScratchReg, dst);
4589 }
4590 } else {
4591 DCHECK(destination->IsFPRegister());
4592 FloatRegister dst = g.ToSingleRegister(destination);
4593 __ Move(dst, src.ToFloat32());
4594 }
4595 } else {
4596 DCHECK_EQ(Constant::kFloat64, src.type());
4597 DoubleRegister dst = destination->IsFPRegister()
4598 ? g.ToDoubleRegister(destination)
4599 : kScratchDoubleReg;
4600 __ Move(dst, src.ToFloat64().value());
4601 if (destination->IsFPStackSlot()) {
4602 __ Sdc1(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4603 }
4604 }
4605 } else if (source->IsFPRegister()) {
4606 MachineRepresentation rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
4607 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4608 CpuFeatureScope msa_scope(masm(), MIPS_SIMD);
4609 MSARegister src = g.ToSimd128Register(source);
4610 if (destination->IsSimd128Register()) {
4611 MSARegister dst = g.ToSimd128Register(destination);
4612 __ move_v(dst, src);
4613 } else {
4614 DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
4615 __ st_b(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4616 }
4617 } else {
4618 FPURegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
4619 if (destination->IsFPRegister()) {
4620 FPURegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
4621 __ Move(dst, src);
4622 } else {
4623 DCHECK(destination->IsFPStackSlot());
4624 __ Sdc1(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4625 }
4626 }
4627 } else if (source->IsFPStackSlot()) {
4628 DCHECK(destination->IsFPRegister() || destination->IsFPStackSlot());
4629 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source);
4630 MachineRepresentation rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
4631 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4632 CpuFeatureScope msa_scope(masm(), MIPS_SIMD);
4633 if (destination->IsSimd128Register()) {
4634 __ ld_b(g.ToSimd128Register(destination), src);
4635 } else {
4636 DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
4637 MSARegister temp = kSimd128ScratchReg;
4638 __ ld_b(temp, src);
4639 __ st_b(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4640 }
4641 } else {
4642 if (destination->IsFPRegister()) {
4643 __ Ldc1(g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), src);
4644 } else {
4645 DCHECK(destination->IsFPStackSlot());
4646 FPURegister temp = kScratchDoubleReg;
4647 __ Ldc1(temp, src);
4648 __ Sdc1(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
4649 }
4650 }
4651 } else {
4652 UNREACHABLE();
4653 }
4654}
4655
4656void CodeGenerator::AssembleSwap(InstructionOperand* source,
4657 InstructionOperand* destination) {
4658 MipsOperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
4659 // Dispatch on the source and destination operand kinds. Not all
4660 // combinations are possible.
4661 if (source->IsRegister()) {
4662 // Register-register.
4663 Register temp = kScratchReg;
4664 Register src = g.ToRegister(source);
4665 if (destination->IsRegister()) {
4666 Register dst = g.ToRegister(destination);
4667 __ Move(temp, src);
4668 __ Move(src, dst);
4669 __ Move(dst, temp);
4670 } else {
4671 DCHECK(destination->IsStackSlot());
4672 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination);
4673 __ mov(temp, src);
4674 __ Ld(src, dst);
4675 __ Sd(temp, dst);
4676 }
4677 } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
4678 DCHECK(destination->IsStackSlot());
4679 Register temp_0 = kScratchReg;
4680 Register temp_1 = kScratchReg2;
4681 MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source);
4682 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination);
4683 __ Ld(temp_0, src);
4684 __ Ld(temp_1, dst);
4685 __ Sd(temp_0, dst);
4686 __ Sd(temp_1, src);
4687 } else if (source->IsFPRegister()) {
4688 MachineRepresentation rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
4689 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4690 CpuFeatureScope msa_scope(masm(), MIPS_SIMD);
4691 MSARegister temp = kSimd128ScratchReg;
4692 MSARegister src = g.ToSimd128Register(source);
4693 if (destination->IsSimd128Register()) {
4694 MSARegister dst = g.ToSimd128Register(destination);
4695 __ move_v(temp, src);
4696 __ move_v(src, dst);
4697 __ move_v(dst, temp);
4698 } else {
4699 DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
4700 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination);
4701 __ move_v(temp, src);
4702 __ ld_b(src, dst);
4703 __ st_b(temp, dst);
4704 }
4705 } else {
4706 FPURegister temp = kScratchDoubleReg;
4707 FPURegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
4708 if (destination->IsFPRegister()) {
4709 FPURegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
4710 __ Move(temp, src);
4711 __ Move(src, dst);
4712 __ Move(dst, temp);
4713 } else {
4714 DCHECK(destination->IsFPStackSlot());
4715 MemOperand dst = g.ToMemOperand(destination);
4716 __ Move(temp, src);
4717 __ Ldc1(src, dst);
4718 __ Sdc1(temp, dst);
4719 }
4720 }
4721 } else if (source->IsFPStackSlot()) {
4722 DCHECK(destination->IsFPStackSlot());
4723 Register temp_0 = kScratchReg;
4724 MemOperand src0 = g.ToMemOperand(source);
4725 MemOperand src1(src0.rm(), src0.offset() + kInt64Size);
4726 MemOperand dst0 = g.ToMemOperand(destination);
4727 MemOperand dst1(dst0.rm(), dst0.offset() + kInt64Size);
4728 MachineRepresentation rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
4729 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
4730 CpuFeatureScope msa_scope(masm(), MIPS_SIMD);
4731 MSARegister temp_1 = kSimd128ScratchReg;
4732 __ ld_b(temp_1, dst0); // Save destination in temp_1.
4733 __ Ld(temp_0, src0); // Then use temp_0 to copy source to destination.
4734 __ Sd(temp_0, dst0);
4735 __ Ld(temp_0, src1);
4736 __ Sd(temp_0, dst1);
4737 __ st_b(temp_1, src0);
4738 } else {
4739 FPURegister temp_1 = kScratchDoubleReg;
4740 __ Ldc1(temp_1, dst0); // Save destination in temp_1.
4741 __ Ld(temp_0, src0); // Then use temp_0 to copy source to destination.
4742 __ Sdc1(temp_1, src0);
4743 __ Sd(temp_0, dst0);
4744 }
4745 } else {
4746 // No other combinations are possible.
4747 UNREACHABLE();
4748 }
4749}
